data.content:
## What Breaks in .NET 11

In EF Core 11, the **sync-over-async opt-in for the Cosmos DB provider is removed entirely**. The temporary compatibility shim (`CosmosDbContextOptionsBuilder.AllowSynchronousIO()` / `EnableSyncOverAsync`) that let synchronous LINQ operators work by blocking on async calls no longer exists.

All four of your methods will throw `InvalidOperationException` at runtime:

| Method | Throws because |
|--------|---------------|
| `ToList()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `First()` | Sync enumeration removed |
| `Count()` | Sync aggregation removed |
| `SaveChanges()` | Sync persist removed |

## The Fix — convert to async

```csharp
public class ProductRepository
{
    private readonly CosmosDbContext _context;

    public async Task<List<Product>> GetAllAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.ToListAsync();
    }

    public async Task<Product> GetByIdAsync(int id)
    {
        return await _context.Products.FirstAsync(p => p.Id == id);
    }

    public async Task<int> GetCountAsync()
    {
        return await _context.Products.CountAsync();
    }

    public async Task SaveAsync(Product product)
    {
        _context.Products.Add(product);
        await _context.SaveChangesAsync();
    }
}
```

**Key takeaways:**
- There is no configuration flag to restore the old behavior — async is now mandatory for Cosmos.
- Callers of these methods must also be updated to `await` the results (async propagates up the call stack).
- `Add()` remains synchronous (it's an in-memory tracking operation, no I/O).
